trans-unit.target: 提供一組方法，這些方法會用於查詢實作 ParallelQuery{TSource} 的物件。

trans-unit.source: This is the parallel equivalent of <see cref="T:System.Linq.Enumerable" />.
trans-unit.target: 在平行查詢方面，這些方法相當於 <see cref="T:System.Linq.Enumerable" />。

trans-unit.target: 轉換後的最終累加值。

trans-unit.source: This overload is specific to parallelized queries.
trans-unit.target: 這個多載會因平行化的查詢。

trans-unit.source: A parallelized query may partition the data source sequence into several sub-sequences (partitions).
trans-unit.target: 平行化的查詢可能會分割成幾個子序列 （資料分割） 資料來源序列。

trans-unit.source: The `updateAccumulatorFunc` is invoked on each element within partitions.
trans-unit.target: `updateAccumulatorFunc`資料分割中的每個項目上叫用。

trans-unit.source: Each partition then yields a single accumulated result.
trans-unit.target: 每個資料分割，然後產生單一的累加的結果。

trans-unit.source: The `combineAccumulatorsFunc` is then invoked on the results of each partition to yield a single element.
trans-unit.target: `combineAccumulatorsFunc`然後結果的每個資料分割，以產生單一項目上叫用。

trans-unit.source: This element is then transformed by the `resultSelector` function.
trans-unit.target: 這個項目則轉換的`resultSelector`函式。

trans-unit.source: This overload of the Any method causes a fully-buffered merge to be performed before the result is returned.
trans-unit.target: 這個方法多載，任何會導致完整緩衝處理的合併，以傳回結果之前執行。

trans-unit.source: The merge behavior can impact performance or cause an out of memory exception in large enumerables.
trans-unit.target: 合併行為可以會影響效能或記憶體不足例外狀況會導致大型的可列舉值。

trans-unit.source: To avoid the merge behavior, use the overload of Any that takes a Func parameter, or else use an alternative method such as FirstOrDefault.
trans-unit.target: 若要避免合併行為，使用任何參數的函式多載，或是使用例如 FirstOrDefault 替代方法。

trans-unit.source: Enables treatment of a data source as if it were ordered, overriding the default of unordered.
trans-unit.target: 覆寫未排序的預設值，將資料來源當做已排序來處理。

trans-unit.source: AsOrdered may only be invoked on non-generic sequences returned by AsParallel, ParallelEnumerable.Range, and ParallelEnumerable.Repeat.
trans-unit.target: 只有在由 AsParallel、ParallelEnumerable.Range 和 ParallelEnumerable.Repeat 傳回的非泛型序列上，才可叫用 AsOrdered。

trans-unit.source: The source sequence which will maintain the original ordering in the subsequent query operators.
trans-unit.target: 將維持後續查詢運算子內原始順序的來源序列。

trans-unit.source: A natural tension exists between performance and preserving order in parallel processing.
trans-unit.target: 效能與保留在平行處理的順序之間不存在的自然的張力。

trans-unit.source: By default, a parallelized query behaves as if the ordering of the results is arbitrary unless AsOrdered is applied or there is an explicit OrderBy operator in the query.
trans-unit.target: 根據預設，平行化的查詢就如同除非 AsOrdered 套用，或在查詢中沒有明確的 OrderBy 運算子結果的順序是任意的。

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Order Preservation in PLINQ](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/order-preservation-in-plinq.md).
trans-unit.target: 如需詳細資訊，請參閱 [PLINQ 中的順序保留](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/order-preservation-in-plinq.md)。

trans-unit.source: Enables parallelization of a query.

trans-unit.source: A partitioner over the input sequence.
trans-unit.target: 輸入序列的 Partitioner。

trans-unit.source: Enables parallelization of a query, as sourced by a custom partitioner that is responsible for splitting the input sequence into partitions.
trans-unit.target: 啟用查詢的平行化作業，此時則指定負責將輸入序列分成多個分割的自訂 Partitioner 處理來源。

trans-unit.source: The <paramref name="source" /> as a ParallelQuery to bind to ParallelEnumerable extension methods.
trans-unit.target: 當 ParallelQuery 繫結到 ParallelEnumerable 擴充方法時的 <paramref name="source" />。

trans-unit.source: The source partitioner's GetOrderedPartitions method is used when ordering is enabled, whereas the partitioner's GetPartitions is used if ordering is not enabled (the default).
trans-unit.target: 來源 partitioner 的 GetOrderedPartitions 排序時，方法使用已啟用，而如果排序不是，則會使用的 partitioner GetPartitions 啟用 （預設值）。

trans-unit.source: The source partitioner's GetDynamicPartitions and GetDynamicOrderedPartitions are not used.
trans-unit.target: 不會使用來源 partitioner 的 GetDynamicPartitions 和 GetDynamicOrderedPartitions。

trans-unit.source: For more information and examples, see [Custom Partitioners for PLINQ and TPL](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/custom-partitioners-for-plinq-and-tpl.md).
trans-unit.target: 如需詳細資訊和範例，請參閱[PLINQ 和 TPL 的自訂 Partitioner](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/custom-partitioners-for-plinq-and-tpl.md)。

trans-unit.source: <paramref name="source" /> is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).
trans-unit.target: <paramref name="source" /> 是 null 參考 (在 Visual Basic 中為 Nothing)。

trans-unit.source: The type of elements of <c>source</c>.
trans-unit.target: 項目的型別<c>來源</c>。

trans-unit.source: The input sequence.
trans-unit.target: 輸入序列。

trans-unit.source: Allows an intermediate query to be treated as if no ordering is implied among the elements.
trans-unit.target: 允許將中繼查詢當做項目之中未套用順序的方式來進行處理。

trans-unit.source: The source sequence with arbitrary order.
trans-unit.target: 具有任意順序的來源序列。

trans-unit.source: AsUnordered may provide performance benefits when ordering is not required in a portion of a query.
trans-unit.target: AsUnordered 查詢部分中不需要排序時，可能會提供效能優勢。

trans-unit.source: By default, PLINQ treats an input sequence as unordered unless OrderBy or AsOrdered is specified.
trans-unit.target: 根據預設，PLINQ 視為序列之輸入的序列排序除非已指定 OrderBy 或 AsOrdered。

trans-unit.source: However, if ordering was turned on and is no longer needed, then AsUnordered can be used to turn it off in mid-query, and this may result in performance benefits.The AsUnordered operator itself does not shuffle the source sequence; it simply removes the ordering requirement for subsequent operators.
trans-unit.target: 不過，如果排序已開啟且不再需要然後 AsUnordered 可用來在中間的查詢中，將它關閉，這可能會導致效能優勢。AsUnordered 運算子本身隨機來源序列中，未執行它只會移除對於後續運算子順序的需求。

trans-unit.source: If the source is ordered, subsequent operators might keep that ordering if it is more efficient to do so.
trans-unit.target: 如果來源經過排序，後續的運算子可能會保留該順序，如果是更有效率，若要這樣做。

trans-unit.source: AsUnordered can be called anywhere in the query; it does not need to be called immediately after AsParallel.
trans-unit.target: AsUnordered 時，才能呼叫任何位置查詢。不需要在 AsParallel 之後立即呼叫。

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Understanding Speedup in PLINQ](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/understanding-speedup-in-plinq.md) and [Order Preservation in PLINQ](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/order-preservation-in-plinq.md).
trans-unit.target: 如需詳細資訊，請參閱[PLINQ 中的了解加速](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/understanding-speedup-in-plinq.md)和[PLINQ 中的順序保留](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/order-preservation-in-plinq.md)。

trans-unit.source: This overload always throws a <see cref="T:System.NotSupportedException" />.
trans-unit.target: 這個多載一定會擲回 <see cref="T:System.NotSupportedException" />。

trans-unit.source: This overload exists to disallow usage of Concat with a left data source of type <xref:System.Linq.ParallelQuery%601> and a right data source of type <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601>.
trans-unit.target: 這個多載存在不允許使用 Concat 左邊的資料來源類型為<xref:System.Linq.ParallelQuery%601>和正確的資料來源類型的<xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601>。

trans-unit.source: Otherwise, the Concat operator would appear to be binding to the parallel implementation, but would in reality bind to the sequential implementation.
trans-unit.target: 否則，Concat 運算子看起來會繫結至平行實作中，但會事實上繫結至循序實作。

trans-unit.source: This overload always throws a <see cref="T:System.NotSupportedException" />.
trans-unit.target: 這個多載一定會擲回 <see cref="T:System.NotSupportedException" />。

trans-unit.source: This overload exists to disallow usage of Union with a left data source of type <xref:System.Linq.ParallelQuery%601> and a right data source of type <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601>.
trans-unit.target: 這個多載存在不允許使用等位的左的資料來源類型為<xref:System.Linq.ParallelQuery%601>和正確的資料來源類型的<xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601>。

trans-unit.source: Otherwise, the Union operator would appear to be binding to the parallel implementation, but would in reality bind to sequential implementation.
trans-unit.target: 否則，Union 運算子看起來會繫結至平行實作中，但會事實上繫結至循序實作。
